{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_55","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating key mapping issues**\n\nI’m noticing that many handlers only recognize Key.Return, while some include a/A as well. On the home screen, it's just Return and space, but the controller maps A to KEY_ENTER rather than to the character A, which might be causing issues. If wtype emits Return or Key.Enter, it should work on Linux too. I need to check if Key.Enter exists in the Slint key enum and might need to fix the home selection to recognize it and other inputs.\n**Addressing key handling issues**\n\nI’m thinking about possibly fixing the content-row and other nested elements, as they might not be utilized since home handles all the keys. However, making changes there could disrupt the detail and library functions. I should focus on one issue at a time, starting with the controller A not selecting on the Home screen, which requires a minimal patch to the Home key handler. I also need to check for AGENTS files in subdirectories to ensure compliance. I'll run a quick search for those files."}}
